Step-by-Step Walkthrough

Step 1: Initial Access
Open your browser and navigate to the IP address of the deployed machine (e.g., http://10.10.51.141). You will be greeted by a stylized, superhero-themed landing page

.

Step 2: Navigate to the Login Page
From the landing page, click on the "Login" button, usually located in the top navigation bar

. This will take you to a page with a simple username and password form.

Step 3: View the Page Source
The login form might look normal, but it behaves suspiciously (e.g., checking credentials without a network request). This indicates client-side validation

.

    Right-click anywhere on the login page and select "View Page Source" (or press Ctrl+U on your keyboard)

    .

Step 4: Find the Hardcoded Credentials
In the page source, look for a block of JavaScript code. You will find a conditional statement that looks like this:
javascript

if (a.value=="h3ck3rBoi" & b.value==RevereString("54321@terceSrepuS"))

This reveals two crucial pieces of information:

    The Username is h3ck3rBoi.

    The Password is the reversed version of 54321@terceSrepuS.

Step 5: Reverse the Password String
The function RevereString (a typo, likely meant to be ReverseString) takes a string and reverses the order of its characters

. To get the actual password, you need to reverse 54321@terceSrepuS.

    You can do this easily in a Linux terminal using the rev command:
    bash

echo "54321@terceSrepuS" | rev

The output will be the password: SuperSecret@12345

    .

Step 6: Log In and Capture the Flag
Go back to the login page and enter the credentials you found:

    Username: h3ck3rBoi

    Password: SuperSecret@12345

Press enter. Upon successful login, you will be redirected to a new page that displays the flag

.

